    "■ D.3 Proof of Lemma 3Note that ∇ θ log π θ (a | s) can be expressed entry-wise as∂ log π θ (a | s) ∂θ s ′,a ′ = 1 [s = s ′] (1 [a = a ′] -π θ (a ′ | s)),(72)which implies∥∇ θ log π θ (a | s)∥ 2 ≤ ∥∇ θ log π θ (a | s)∥ 1 ≤ 1 + 1 = 2.",
    "(73)By the definition of F,∥F (θ, µ, V f, s, a, b, s ′)∥ ≤ ∥∇ θ log π θ (a | s)∥ r f (s, a, b, µ) + τ E(π θ, s) + γV f (s ′) -V f (s) ≤ 2(1 + τ log |A| + γB V + B V) = 2(1 + γ)B V + 2τ log |A| + 2,where the second inequality applies (73).By a similar argument, we can show∥D(ω, µ, V l, s, b, s ′)∥ ≤ 2(1 + γ)B V + 2.For H, we have∥H(µ, s)∥ = ∥e s -µ∥ ≤ ∥e s ∥ + ∥µ∥ ≤ 2.For the G operators,∥G f (θ, µ, V f, s, a, b, s ′)∥ ≤ ∥e s ∥ r f (s, a, b, µ) + τ E(π θ, s) + γV f (s ′) -V f (s) ≤ 1 • (1 + τ log |A| + γB V + B V) = (1 + γ)B V + τ log |A| + 1.",
    "Similarly, ∥G l (ω, µ, V l, s, b, s ′)∥ ≤ (1 + γ)B V + 1.",
    "■ D.4 Proof of Lemma 4By the definition of F,∥ F (θ 1, ω 1, µ 1, V 1) -F (θ 2, ω 2, µ 2, V 2)∥ = ∥E s∼d π θ 1, ϕω 1, µ 1 ρ,a∼π θ 1 (•|s),b∼ϕω 1 (•|s),s ′ ∼P µ 1 (•|s,a,b) [F (θ 1, µ 1, V 1, s, a, b, s ′)] -E s∼d π θ 2, ϕω 2, µ 2 ρ,a∼π θ 2 (•|s),b∼ϕω 2 (•|s),s ′ ∼P µ 2 (•|s,a,b) [F (θ 2, µ 2, V 2, s, a, b, s ′)]∥ = s,a,b,s ′ d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)π θ1 (a | s)ϕ ω1 (b | s)P µ1 (s ′ | s, a, b) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)π θ2 (a | s)ϕ ω2 (b | s)P µ2 (s ′ | s, a) F (θ 2, µ 2, V 2, s, a, b, s ′) + E s∼d π θ 1, ϕω 1, µ 1 ρ,a∼π θ 1 (•|s),b∼ϕω 1 (•|s),s ′ ∼P µ 1 (•|s,a,b) [F (θ 1, µ 1, V 1, s, a, b, s ′) -F (θ 2, µ 2, V 2, s, a, b, s ′)] ≤ E s∼d π θ 1, ϕω 1, µ 1 ρ,a∼π θ 1 (•|s),b∼ϕω 1 (•|s),s ′ ∼P µ 1 (•|s,a,b) [F (θ 1, µ 1, V 1, s, a, b, s ′) -F (θ 2, µ 2, V 2, s, a, b, s ′)] + B F s,a,b,s ′ d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)π θ1 (a | s)ϕ ω1 (b | s)P µ1 (s ′ | s, a, b) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)π θ2 (a | s)ϕ ω2 (b | s)P µ2 (s ′ | s, a) ≤ E s∼d π θ 1, ϕω 1, µ 1 ρ,a∼π θ 1 (•|s),b∼ϕω 1 (•|s),s ′ ∼P µ 1 (•|s,a,b) [F (θ 1, µ 1, V 1, s, a, b, s ′) -F (θ 2, µ 2, V 2, s, a, b, s ′)] + B F s,s ′ d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)P π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 (s ′ | s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)P π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 (s ′ | s).",
    "(74)To bound the first term of (74),∥F (θ 1, µ 1, V 1, s, a, b, s ′) -F (θ 2, µ 2, V 2, s, a, b, s ′)∥ = ∥∇ θ log π θ1 (a | s)(r f (s, a, b, µ 1) + τ E(π θ1, s) + γV 1 (s ′) -V 1 (s)) -∇ θ log π θ2 (a | s)(r f (s, a, b, µ 2) + τ E(π θ2, s) + γV 2 (s ′) -V 2 (s))∥ ≤ ∥∇ θ log π θ1 (a | s) -∇ θ log π θ2 (a | s)∥ r f (s, a, b, µ 1) + τ E(π θ1, s) + γV 1 (s ′) -V 1 (s) + ∥∇ θ log π θ2 (a | s)∥ r f (s, a, b, µ 1) -r f (s, a, b, µ 2) + τ E(π θ1, s) -τ E(π θ2, s) + γV 1 (s ′) -γV 2 (s ′) -V 1 (s) + V 2 (s)) ≤ ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥(1 + τ log |A| + (1 + γ)B V) + 2 L r |µ 1 -µ 2 | + (4 + 8 log |A|)τ (1 -γ) 3 ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + (1 + γ)∥V 1 -V 2 ∥ ≤ 1 + τ log |A| + (1 + γ)B V + (4 + 8 log |A|)τ (1 -γ) 3 ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + 2L r ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + 2(1 + γ)∥V 1 -V 2 ∥,(75)where the second inequality is due to Lipschitz continuity of the entropy function (see Zeng et al. [2022][Lemma 6]) and the boundedness and 1-Lipschitz continuity of ∇ θ log π θ, which is obvious from ( 72) and ( 73).By Lemma 2, we have for the second term of ( 74),B F s,s ′ d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)P π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 (s ′ | s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)P π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 (s ′ | s) ≤ B F s d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)P π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 (• | s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)P π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 (• | s) ≤ B F 1 -γ L P ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥."
