  "correct_citations": [
    "(74)To bound the first term of (74),∥F (θ 1, µ 1, V 1, s, a, b, s ′) -F (θ 2, µ 2, V 2, s, a, b, s ′)∥ = ∥∇ θ log π θ1 (a | s)(r f (s, a, b, µ 1) + τ E(π θ1, s) + γV 1 (s ′) -V 1 (s)) -∇ θ log π θ2 (a | s)(r f (s, a, b, µ 2) + τ E(π θ2, s) + γV 2 (s ′) -V 2 (s))∥ ≤ ∥∇ θ log π θ1 (a | s) -∇ θ log π θ2 (a | s)∥ r f (s, a, b, µ 1) + τ E(π θ1, s) + γV 1 (s ′) -V 1 (s) + ∥∇ θ log π θ2 (a | s)∥ r f (s, a, b, µ 1) -r f (s, a, b, µ 2) + τ E(π θ1, s) -τ E(π θ2, s) + γV 1 (s ′) -γV 2 (s ′) -V 1 (s) + V 2 (s)) ≤ ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥(1 + τ log |A| + (1 + γ)B V) + 2 L r |µ 1 -µ 2 | + (4 + 8 log |A|)τ (1 -γ) 3 ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + (1 + γ)∥V 1 -V 2 ∥ ≤ 1 + τ log |A| + (1 + γ)B V + (4 + 8 log |A|)τ (1 -γ) 3 ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + 2L r ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + 2(1 + γ)∥V 1 -V 2 ∥,(75)where the second inequality is due to Lipschitz continuity of the entropy function (see Zeng et al. [2022][Lemma 6]) and the boundedness and 1-Lipschitz continuity of ∇ θ log π θ, which is obvious from ( 72) and ( 73).By Lemma 2, we have for the second term of ( 74),B F s,s ′ d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)P π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 (s ′ | s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)P π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 (s ′ | s) ≤ B F s d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)P π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 (• | s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)P π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 (• | s) ≤ B F 1 -γ L P ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥."
